<subSubSection id="9EEF6552FFA00C20B9E0E098D373FD92" pageId="8" pageNumber="51" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D64A36D9FFA00C20B9E0E098D373FD92" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="E481EACBFFA00C20B9E0E098D310FE7E" bold="true" box="[199,334,474,500]" pageId="8" pageNumber="51">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName id="11F54D5AFFA00C20B8EAE098D03DFE7E" authorityName="Turan &amp; Kottelat &amp; Kaya" authorityYear="2022" box="[461,611,474,500]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Salmonidae" genus="Salmo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Salmoniformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ardahanensis">
<emphasis id="E481EACBFFA00C20B8EAE098D03DFE7E" box="[461,611,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="51">ardahanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from 
<collectingRegion id="1431F83BFFA00C20BA3AE098D1B5FE7E" box="[797,1003,474,500]" country="Turkey" name="Ardahan" pageId="8" pageNumber="51">Ardahan Province</collectingRegion>
, where the species has been collected. An adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
